1
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:25,080
Hello, Arnon.

2
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,360
Arnon…

3
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,920
Grandma.

4
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,320
I don't understand.

5
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:07,840
Don't tell me you believe him.

6
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,160
I've seen the documents. I already know.

7
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:13,680
- And?
- It's not that I believe Jirasin.

8
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,800
Then why did you let him go like that?

9
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,480
Rat,

10
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:20,920
if we're going to be the kind of people
who can manage others,

11
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,520
we have to balance authority and mercy.

12
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,240
Don't forget that Jirasin

13
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,720
can still be very useful to us.

14
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:33,560
Right now,
you've already used authority with him.

15
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,760
So I have to use mercy.

16
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,680
Most importantly,

17
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:43,400
I believe that right now,
Jirasin wouldn't dare step out of line.

18
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:47,520
Because he knows you're watching him.

19
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:52,640
And more importantly, Jirasin's work
will have to come out well too.

20
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:55,400
Because he wants to prove to me

21
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,760
that he's capable, that he has value,
and that he's loyal.

22
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,680
To manage people,

23
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:05,920
you don't need to say everything you know.

24
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:10,840
What matters
is knowing the right moment to say it.

25
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,440
But I don't understand.

26
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,760
Why do you always give in to Jirasin?

27
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,920
How's the child?

28
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,000
Has he had medicine yet?

29
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,720
If there's anything we can help with,

30
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,880
just let us know.

31
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:43,000
Anything at all.

32
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,240
Because I don't want this child to grow up

33
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:52,040
feeling like
life has gone wrong in every way.

34
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,880
You need to understand, Rat.

35
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:12,120
Everyone's origin
and background is different.

36
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:18,160
You can't use one ruler
to judge the whole world.

37
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:22,240
People are born different.
They think differently.

38
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:24,800
Their lives are not the same.

39
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,600
But if you're going to let things happen

40
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:31,400
and keep pretending not to see them,

41
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,000
that won't work, Grandma.

42
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:37,000
Everything has its ending.

43
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:41,600
It just depends on
how we choose to let it end.

44
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:45,040
And I don't see why

45
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:48,600
this has to end as a tragedy.

46
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:52,080
That's what she said.

47
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:56,640
I still have another concern
about fraudulent transactions.

48
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,960
Jirasin shouldn't be
holding Vanich shares.

49
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,440
What do you think?

50
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,520
Jirasin shouldn't be
holding any shares at all.

51
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,440
Do you have any good ideas?

52
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,600
You suddenly got so many Vanich shares.

53
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,600
You really are impressive.

54
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,960
Patience always pays off.

55
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,040
And the payoff is well worth it.

56
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,440
What's your next move?

57
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:42,400
Next, we need to make sure the new CEO
goes to inspect the site.

58
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,440
Hello?

59
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,640
Mr. Golf?

60
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,400
Oh, Kluay, you're awake?

61
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,600
I think I'm going to stop by the office.

62
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:07,160
Why? Is there urgent work?

63
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,760
No.

64
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:11,880
But I don't know if I'm imagining it,
about Mr. Warat.

65
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,600
What now?

66
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:17,360
I feel like he's acting strange.

67
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:19,280
Like he's hiding something.

68
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:22,720
There's nothing.
You're overthinking again.

69
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,960
I think you should go back and rest.

70
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,800
No, I'm already awake.

71
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,960
And I can't stop worrying.

72
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,840
If you're going, fine.
But I'm going with you.

73
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:39,400
Then before we go, sit down.
Let me eat a little more.

74
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Okay.

75
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,760
Want some?

76
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,600
- Thank you for letting me come in.
- Of course.

77
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:08,800
You already know
about Ameena and Warat, right?

78
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,040
Roughly.

79
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:14,880
About these two…

80
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:15,800
I understand.

81
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:21,120
But actually, didn't Ameena
already have a boyfriend?

82
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,560
So how did she end up with Warat?

83
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:27,560
I don't know
what exactly is going on between them.

84
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,880
We'll probably have to let them
sort it out themselves.

85
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:34,280
But Ameena told me
that the baby in her womb…

86
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,559
If she said that,

87
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,840
then we'll have to get clarity on it,

88
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,880
so both sides can have peace of mind.

89
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,880
Mrs. Wanee.

90
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:49,120
I have a reputation in society too.

91
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:54,120
I don't want people saying
my daughter is pregnant with no father.

92
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,400
Oh, you don't have to worry about that.

93
00:08:56,480 --> 00:09:00,320
If the child in her womb
really is Warat's,

94
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:03,640
we are willing
to take full responsibility.

95
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,920
I have to apologize, Grandma.

96
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:12,360
I really didn't want
something like this to happen.

97
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:14,640
You don't need to apologize.

98
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,520
You didn't do anything wrong.

99
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,840
I think for now,

100
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:25,360
it would be better
if we focused on finding a solution.

101
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:29,560
But this is such a big matter,

102
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:33,360
Warat should be here to hear it too.

103
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,960
How about this?

104
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:39,200
Let's have dinner together this evening.

105
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:42,360
That way, I can bring Warat too.

106
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:45,040
Most importantly,
I think it would be better

107
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:48,560
if the two of them talked directly

108
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:51,280
and figured out a way through this.

109
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,280
That'd be better.

110
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,520
Alright.

111
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:20,120
Is there anything you want to tell me?

112
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,280
Don't ever go
looking for me like that again.

113
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:35,360
Then you're not allowed
to disappear like that again either, okay?

114
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,280
I'm sorry.

115
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,360
I forgive you.

116
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:44,960
I never wanted things
to turn out like this, Kluay.

117
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:50,200
Is there anything else that I should know?

118
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:55,840
Well, I'm not Mr. Wichan's son.

119
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,000
Then…

120
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,080
whose son are you?

121
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,920
It feels like
I've been lying to you this whole time.

122
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:13,520
But I swear I never meant to. I'm sorry.

123
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,080
It's okay.

124
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,240
It's such a small thing.

125
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:20,280
I'm not thinking too much about it.

126
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,600
- I'm going to find Waree.
- Mm.

127
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,920
- And…
- I'm going to return everything to her.

128
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,720
She's the real Vanich heir.

129
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,360
And after that?

130
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,520
Then at that point,

131
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,680
I might end up with nothing at all.

132
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,520
Mm.

133
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,200
That's okay.

134
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:44,800
I don't care about that at all.

135
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:48,040
I don't care if you are a somebody
or what kind of family you come from.

136
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:51,200
So, whose son are you?

137
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,960
I'm Mr. Sarut's son.

138
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,840
Hm, no, you're not.

139
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:03,160
Maybe it's just a coincidence.

140
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,720
You are Mr. Warat.

141
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:09,200
Mr. Wichan's son, Mrs. Wanee's grandson.

142
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:13,360
And maybe you just happen
to have a little of Mr. Sarut's blood.

143
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,760
But it's not right.

144
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:21,600
I… I shouldn't accept things that…

145
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:25,040
aren't mine. You get what I mean?

146
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,640
Why not?

147
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:30,840
Everything, the will,

148
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:34,320
the assets, this mall.

149
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:38,160
If you don't want it,
you can just return it to Grandma.

150
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,000
Does she know the truth yet?

151
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,840
She does.

152
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:47,680
And did she kick you out
or ask for everything back?

153
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,600
No.

154
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:54,280
See? That means
she loves you for who you are.

155
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,920
It has nothing to do with

156
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,640
whether you have
the family's blood or not.

157
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,760
Just like how I love you.

158
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,800
I love you for who you are.

159
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:08,680
It doesn't matter
whether you have wealth or not.

160
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,080
- Really?
- Mm.

161
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:19,400
But I also have something
to talk to you about.

162
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,160
Yesterday, Ameena came
to see me while you were gone.

163
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,480
Why?

164
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,800
She wanted to talk to you…

165
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:34,360
about the baby.

166
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,480
The baby?

167
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:42,200
She said you got her pregnant.

168
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,800
- Me?
- Mm.

169
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,360
Uh, Mr. Warat,

170
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:51,920
Mrs. Wanee would like to see you.

171
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,960
- Is something wrong?
- It's about Ms. Ameena.

172
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:56,640
What about her?

173
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,560
CONTACT PHOTO AND POSTER

174
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,200
There's a delivery for you.

175
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,840
CALL

176
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,920
Thank you.

177
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,600
SOM

178
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,960
Hello, Arnon.

179
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,880
Even though

180
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,160
it's not much,

181
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:27,320
it's something I got within my means.

182
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:32,920
I hope this pendant
can represent my feelings for you.

183
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,280
<i>If you don't mind,</i>

184
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,920
<i>will you be my girlfriend?</i>

185
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:41,800
Arnon…

186
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,520
Yes!

187
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:05,800
So, you've seen the new
shareholder structure of Vanich.

188
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,480
What do you think?

189
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:10,080
In my opinion,

190
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,880
Mr. Warat is in danger.

191
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,000
In what way?

192
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:18,480
If you, the second-largest shareholder,

193
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,440
wants to take over everything,

194
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,040
it would be very easy.

195
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,400
Grandma must trust that

196
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:28,080
- I wouldn't do something like that.
- Yes.

197
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:32,000
So she gave me quite a lot of shares…

198
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:35,640
thinking that I wouldn't betray Warat.

199
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:38,680
If I wanted to become
the majority shareholder

200
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:43,720
and make you
the new executive instead of Warat,

201
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:48,640
would that be an interesting idea?

202
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,480
And what do you want?

203
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:54,080
When we hold shares in a company,

204
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,520
we want to see profit, right?

205
00:15:57,520 --> 00:16:02,360
I just want to own a company
with the right management.

206
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:05,360
Someone who earns
the position through ability,

207
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,400
not connections.

208
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,080
So how can I help you?

209
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,360
If I acquire all your shares,

210
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,720
I'll become the majority shareholder.

211
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:36,640
Then I'll remove Warat

212
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,320
and appoint you in his place.

213
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:43,360
- And…
- A company at this level,

214
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,760
if you become the executive,

215
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,400
imagine how much the stock would rise.

216
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:51,520
When everything is settled,

217
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:54,240
I'll sell the shares back to you
at the original price

218
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,320
if you want.

219
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:03,200
When will you start the process
of removing Warat?

220
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:07,040
It already started even
before Grandma announced the will.

221
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,040
Grandma.

222
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,400
Ameena came earlier.

223
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:29,720
- Yes, Grandma.
- What happened?

224
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,680
Nothing.

225
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,160
Nothing?

226
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:35,520
Then why did her father come and say…

227
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,360
That I slept with her?

228
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,560
And what's the truth?

229
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:43,200
Maybe I'm actually
suitable for Ameena, Grandma.

230
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:46,640
Warat, does that mean

231
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:49,560
you really got her pregnant?

232
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:52,760
If you did,
you have to take responsibility.

233
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:01,600
Kluay.

234
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,360
What did Grandma say?

235
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:13,080
Huh? What did you say?

236
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,600
What exactly happened that night?

237
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,000
Mm…

238
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:20,800
What did you say?

239
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,200
What did Grandma say?

240
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,040
She just said…

241
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:36,800
if it's true,
I have to take responsibility. Kluay,

242
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,360
I don't remember anything at all.

243
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,880
Okay, I understand.

244
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,600
Kluay, no, you don't really understand.

245
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,800
But no matter what, it already happened.

246
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:54,280
You have to take responsibility.

247
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:57,440
Take care of her family well.

248
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,680
Kluay, it's… it's not like that.

249
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:03,520
You know I don't feel anything for Ameena.

250
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,480
Not even a little.

251
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,640
You know that, right?

252
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,720
Whether you feel something or not
doesn't matter.

253
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,880
What matters is you already did it.

254
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,680
Did what? I didn't do anything.

255
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:19,640
Are you sure about that?

256
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,280
I didn't do it.

257
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,840
I'm sure

258
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:31,680
that Ameena drugged me.

259
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,160
This was her plan.

260
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:37,760
I wasn't conscious.
I don't remember anything.

261
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,440
Okay.

262
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,920
I'll tell you.

263
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,640
When I walked…

264
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:50,320
into that bar, I asked her, "Ameena,

265
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:53,800
where's Kluay?"
She said you were in the room

266
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:56,800
waiting for me. Then I drank water.

267
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,280
Yes, I drank water.

268
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:03,320
And I was just passed out.

269
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,600
I can't remember anything.

270
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,560
Seriously, Kluay.

271
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,680
It was her plan.

272
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,440
But no matter what, it already happened.

273
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:19,600
What if the baby is yours?

274
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,760
What baby? Kluay, it's…

275
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:27,160
I didn't do anything.

276
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:32,360
Okay, the baby, right?

277
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,280
If that child is really mine,
I'll take responsibility.

278
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,640
But it has nothing to do with Ameena.

279
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:45,120
Every couple

280
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:48,040
faces obstacles.

281
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:51,480
And we do too, right?

282
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:56,680
But what matters is
do we love each other enough?

283
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:01,600
When we face problems,
will we still hold hands like this?

284
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:04,600
Do we still trust each other?

285
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:08,480
See? You're smiling again.

286
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,640
I'm not smiling.

287
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:11,240
You look really cute when you smile.

288
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:14,080
That's it. There's nothing. Okay?

289
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,120
I'll find out the truth.

290
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:20,800
Then I'll find the truth my way too.

291
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:24,280
Okay. I'll find the truth my way as well.

292
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:27,520
- Okay.
- So what truth are you going to look for?

293
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,200
I'm going to talk to Det.

294
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,360
- No, come on.
- Uh, uh.

295
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:34,520
No. Don't talk to him, okay?

296
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:38,280
Why not? You can still talk to Ameena.

297
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,400
Hello, are you there already?

298
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:42,800
Okay, I'll hurry over.

299
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:47,520
Can you promise me something?

300
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:52,120
If anything bad happens, tell me.
Call me immediately, okay?

301
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:54,360
Okay.

302
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:56,640
I'm going.

303
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,400
I'm going.

304
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:23,400
Som.

305
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,760
What are you doing today?

306
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,840
Preparing procurement documents.

307
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,920
Are you free tonight?
Want to have dinner with me?

308
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,200
- I'm not free.
- Where are you going?

309
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,080
I have plans with the kids at home.

310
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,840
- Oh, then I'll go with you.
- No need.

311
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,200
Then how are you getting there?

312
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:43,160
I can go by myself.
You don't have to bother.

313
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:45,560
But I'm free. I can go.

314
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:46,680
You're not free.

315
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,600
What do you want from me, Arnon?

316
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:53,760
- I just…
- If you love her, go with her.

317
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:56,400
What do you take me for?

318
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:01,400
What do you mean?

319
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,160
You bought something for her too.

320
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,280
What did you hear?

321
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:07,600
I heard everything.

322
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:14,240
What, you think I wouldn't know
that you've been talking to someone else?

323
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,240
Som…

324
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,200
I love her.

325
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,800
Do you know

326
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:35,160
how I've felt

327
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:37,920
all this time?

328
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,600
Why are you doing this to me?

329
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:44,800
What am I to you?

330
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:46,920
Don't you see my feelings at all?

331
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:51,960
I'm sorry.

332
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,640
But today,

333
00:23:57,640 --> 00:24:01,920
I was planning
to confess my love to the person I like.

334
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:09,800
Okay.

335
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:12,840
I understand.

336
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:31,840
Will you be my girlfriend?

337
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,240
I'm not rich,

338
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,480
but I'll take the best care of you.

339
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:48,800
What do you mean?

340
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:51,600
Then the person you've been talking to…

341
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,760
I was practicing.

342
00:24:55,520 --> 00:24:57,360
Practicing for you.

343
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,000
Oh…

344
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,000
So? Are you okay with it?

345
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:15,800
Okay with what?

346
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,680
Being my girlfriend.

347
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:23,760
You already know what I'm going to say.

348
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:25,360
How would I know?

349
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,560
What did you ask me again?

350
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,320
Will you be my girlfriend?

351
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,120
What does that mean?

352
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:45,400
Yes.

353
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,120
What does "yes" mean?

354
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:54,880
Ugh, it means I'll be your girlfriend.

355
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:23,120
Yes, Mr. Warat.

356
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,280
Oh, okay.

357
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:31,160
Som, head home. And pick up Ms. Kluay too.

358
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:33,640
Go back to the Vanich house.
I'll be late tonight.

359
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:35,840
- Okay.
- Mm.

360
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,720
No.

361
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:43,320
"Okay, darling."

362
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:47,040
You're crazy. Go.

363
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,720
- Darling.
- Go.

364
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:49,760
Darling.

365
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:00,680
Mr. Arnon,

366
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,520
what do you think I should do about Kluay?

367
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,920
What about her?

368
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,440
I feel like I'm taking advantage of her.

369
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,160
Why do you think that?

370
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:14,600
When I asked her to be my girlfriend,

371
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:17,760
I was Warat of the Vanich family.

372
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:19,800
But now that I know

373
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:23,920
I might not be that Warat anymore,

374
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:27,120
I feel like I'm holding her back.

375
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:28,920
So what are you going to do?

376
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,480
I'll find Waree,
return everything to Grandma,

377
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,760
- and go live where I really belong.
- Hey.

378
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:37,560
Wait, you don't have to do that.

379
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:40,960
- I have to. I have to do…
- What?

380
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:42,560
Did Mrs. Wanee kick you out?

381
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,880
- No.
- Right.

382
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:47,200
- Did Ms. Kluay break up with you?
- No.

383
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:49,640
So,

384
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:54,120
why would you do that
when no one wants things

385
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:56,560
to be this way?

386
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,600
I have to do what's right.

387
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:00,640
I have to do it.

388
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,440
- But…
- Ms. Kluay

389
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,880
already told you, didn't she?

390
00:28:03,960 --> 00:28:07,360
That she doesn't want you
to disappear again.

391
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:12,520
Okay. Then this time,
I'll talk to her honestly. Okay?

392
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,040
Mm.

393
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,720
Sis.

394
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,160
You sound cheerful.

395
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:27,800
Let's go home.

396
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:31,440
Oh, it's already evening?

397
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,480
I didn't even check the time.

398
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:38,720
Som, you go home first.
I still have something to do.

399
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:40,600
Something? Wait a second.

400
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:43,080
You never say that to me.

401
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,840
Where are you going?

402
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,160
To see a guy.

403
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:50,560
I just have someone I need to talk to.

404
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:52,120
Who?

405
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:54,160
Det.

406
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:56,600
Det? Again?

407
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,720
Every time you talk to him,
there's trouble.

408
00:28:58,800 --> 00:29:01,160
Haven't you learned?

409
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:05,360
This time it's serious. I have to go.

410
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:07,160
What now?

411
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:09,920
Another problem with that crazy Ameena?

412
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:12,400
Probably not this time.

413
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,520
Why are you so soft-hearted?

414
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,480
How can you believe people like them?

415
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:22,080
Det said he broke up with Ameena.

416
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:25,920
I just want to know what really happened.

417
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:30,280
Fine. I'm going with you.

418
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:33,680
It's Det's personal business.

419
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:35,800
I don't want him to feel uncomfortable.

420
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:38,920
I don't care. I'm going with you.

421
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:41,240
I'll just sit far away.

422
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,000
I'm going.

423
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,560
I don't know Sarut very well,

424
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:57,040
but from what I've seen, I think he knows.

425
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:00,640
<i>- If he already knows, then why…?</i>
- Or…

426
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:04,680
<i>Maybe he's waiting for Mr. Warat</i>
<i>to receive the inheritance first.</i>

427
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:09,200
And if he can prove
that he's really Warat's father,

428
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:13,640
then he himself
will get a share of the inheritance too.

429
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:16,000
<i>With the utmost respect, ma'am,</i>

430
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:18,320
<i>if anything happens to Mr. Warat,</i>

431
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,680
<i>all the assets</i>

432
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:23,440
<i>will be transferred to Mr. Sarut,</i>
<i>his biological father,</i>

433
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:25,680
<i>not returned to you, ma'am.</i>

434
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:36,280
Darling!

435
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:41,600
- Arnon.
- What?

436
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:43,120
Why are you calling me that?

437
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:47,200
Well, we're a couple now.

438
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:50,560
I know, but…

439
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:53,440
it's too soon. It gives me goosebumps.

440
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:57,240
Come on, it's like this at first.
After a while,

441
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:59,520
you'll get used to it, okey-dokey?

442
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:01,800
Stop. Stop right there.

443
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:04,920
- Oh?
- Who taught you to say "okey-dokey"?

444
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:07,440
I heard that

445
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:12,000
when couples say "okey-dokey,"
it sounds cute.

446
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:14,320
Ugh, then I don't want that.

447
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:19,360
Why not, Somnao?

448
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:21,640
Hey, why do I have to be

449
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,280
- "Somnao"?
- Uh…

450
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,480
Arnon, where's the balance?

451
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:27,920
Do you know what moderation is?

452
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:32,040
Okay, got it.

453
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:35,720
So why did Mrs. Wanee call Mr. Warat in?

454
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:41,560
Well, Mr. Warat
is going to break up with Ms. Kluay.

455
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,040
What? Break up?

456
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:46,560
Why would he do that?

457
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:48,960
They love each other so much.

458
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:51,520
Uh, Mr. Warat…

459
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:54,080
What about him? Say it.

460
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,960
He'll tell you himself.

461
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:58,760
Oh, so now you're keeping secrets from me?

462
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:01,280
- No, no…
- We've been together for an hour,

463
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:02,400
and you already have secrets?

464
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:03,920
Oh, is that how it is? Fine.

465
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:06,360
Oh, Som…

466
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:09,400
Hello, Kluay.

467
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:13,480
I'm out now.
You can wait for me at Baan Saeng.

468
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:15,040
And what about Det…?

469
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:16,920
<i>He's not that bad.</i>

470
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,400
I can trust him.

471
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,920
We studied together for five years, okay?

472
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:26,840
Fine.

473
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:29,760
But if anything happens,
call me immediately, okay?

474
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,920
Will she be okay?

475
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:38,320
She'll be fine. If anything happens,
she'll call.

476
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:41,160
Don't go home yet. We'll go back together.

477
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:43,280
Where are you going?

478
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:46,880
I have something important
to discuss with Jirasin.

479
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:04,320
BANK

480
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,480
The money's in, Mr. Chatchai.

481
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,760
You're amazing.

482
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:17,120
I sold it way above market price.

483
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,840
Can't believe someone stupid bought it.

484
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:21,520
If Mr. Golf gets your shares,

485
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:25,040
he'll become the owner of Vanich Mall
instead of Warat. Worth it.

486
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:27,760
- But I think…
- From now on, just sit back,

487
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:30,360
count the money,

488
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:32,360
and watch Warat fall apart.

489
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:48,520
About what you said
that you broke up with Ameena,

490
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:49,560
what's going on?

491
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,080
Yes.

492
00:33:54,560 --> 00:33:56,560
I broke up with her yesterday.

493
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:03,120
But yesterday, Ameena came to see me.

494
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:07,400
She came to see you? Where?

495
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:09,719
Actually,

496
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:12,880
she intended to meet Mrs. Wanee.

497
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:15,360
Mrs. Wanee?

498
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:19,639
But Mrs. Wanee was busy,

499
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:21,719
so,

500
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:24,320
she asked me to pass on
the message instead.

501
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:26,560
What message?

502
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,080
It's not something good.

503
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:37,159
I thought you…

504
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:39,920
might…

505
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:42,760
I know already.

506
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:48,440
Yeah, that.

507
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:54,840
But what Ameena said might not be true.

508
00:34:58,040 --> 00:35:00,840
So you mean Ameena isn't pregnant?

509
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,640
Actually,

510
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:07,480
she probably is pregnant.

511
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,840
But she went to Mrs. Wanee

512
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:17,800
to say the baby

513
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:20,040
is Warat's.

514
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:25,400
You know what?

515
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:28,680
I believe…

516
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:31,600
I believe in my partner.

517
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:39,840
At first, I was angry

518
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,560
when Ameena told me.

519
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:48,800
She told me

520
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:54,080
after calling me just a servant's son.

521
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:57,960
Det…

522
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:02,360
Well…

523
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:07,280
At first I was angry…

524
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:09,880
so I said

525
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:15,120
the baby isn't mine.

526
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:18,480
Det.

527
00:36:19,120 --> 00:36:20,880
But…

528
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:25,160
I know the truth. Actually…

529
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:30,320
the baby is mine.

530
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:35,480
Then just tell Ameena that.

531
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:38,440
This morning,

532
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,080
her father called me.

533
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:46,200
He told me to stay away from her.

534
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:49,880
How is that possible?

535
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:52,160
Because he said

536
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:56,320
the baby is Warat's.

537
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,440
How could that be?

538
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,360
Anything's possible.

539
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:06,120
Her father has already planned everything.

540
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:09,080
So,

541
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:13,240
- what are you going to do?
- Well.

542
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:18,960
Kluay…

543
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:28,800
Can you help me?

544
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,640
I want my family back.

545
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:52,080
Oh, I've known for a long time already
that you two like each other.

546
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:53,800
NEXT EPISODE

547
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:55,840
You call me "bro"? But you lied to me.

548
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:58,200
You lied to everyone! Why?!

549
00:37:58,800 --> 00:37:59,840
I…

550
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:03,840
I didn't want to do this.

551
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:06,200
Did your father tell you to?

552
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:11,600
I think you should start packing now.

553
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:14,120
Because tomorrow, Mr. Warat will fire you.

554
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:15,840
Hit me.

555
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,720
Go on, hit me.

556
00:38:19,040 --> 00:38:20,960
<i>I did what I had to do</i>

557
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,280
to protect Vanich.

558
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,480
